# Verified against: udev(7)
# Reviewed: 2026-06-14

# The internal MediaTek MT7902 (PCI 14c3:7902, "Filogic 310") has no working
# kernel driver before Linux 7.1: mt7921e binds via driver_override but only
# reaches "ASIC revision: 79020000" and never loads firmware, so no interface
# appears. Left alone it stays powered in D0 (no driver, runtime PM off),
# wasting ~1.5-2 W. WiFi is provided by a USB adapter (rtw88_8821au) instead,
# so remove the dead PCIe device at enumeration to let its link power down.
# Revert: delete this rule once Linux 7.1 (native MT7902 support) is installed.
ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="pci", ATTR{vendor}=="0x14c3", ATTR{device}=="0x7902", ATTR{remove}="1"
